cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.SC 

The paper deals with lower bounds and derandomization of arithmetic circuits, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algebraic and combinatorial aspects, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with information theory and communication complexity, which suggest cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) as possible sub-categories.
